The paper discusses model-based reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The focus is on improving the accuracy of predicting future states in sequential environments, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also presents theoretical and empirical results, which suggests that it could be categorized under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). However, the main focus is on improving the performance of machine learning models, which suggests that it is most likely to be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
